# Configuration — No .env File Needed

As of the current version, this toolkit no longer uses a .env file.

Credentials (Slack webhook, Google Sheets, OpenAI key — all optional) are
entered through the app's own Setup screen on first run, or any time
afterward via the "Settings" button in the main window.

Each user's entries are saved locally on their own machine at:

    Windows: %APPDATA%\CSRToolkit\config.json
    Mac:     ~/Library/Application Support/CSRToolkit/config.json
    Linux:   ~/.config/CSRToolkit/config.json

This file is never committed to the repo and is not shared between users —
each person enters their own credentials.

The toolkit works fully offline with zero configuration: keyword matching
plus local CSV logging both work with nothing entered. Slack, Google
Sheets, and OpenAI are optional add-ons, not requirements.

See PACKAGING.md for full setup and build instructions.

This file is kept only as a placeholder so the repo structure stays
familiar; it is not read by the application.
